1332. To CHRISTOPHER OF UTENHEIM.

Opus Epistolarum p. 815. Basle. N. p. 779: Lond. xxi. 8: LB. 661. <Jan. init> 1523.

[As the mouth-date is missing, it is likely that the year-date was added at the time of printing. Obviously 1522—3 are the only years possible. There are some resemblances to Ep. 1311 ; but the decision to stay at Basle till March, conflicts with the wish expressed in Ep. 1311. 37-40, 1101 10 winter there. It may be com- pared with the intention shown in Epp. 1319. 16-17‚ 1327. 11-12, 10 see the winter out before moving. The hesitation of the utterances here about the new Pope no doubt implies that Ep. 1324 had not yet arrived: so that this letter may be placed at any date between 25 Dee. 1522 (with a year beginning at Christmas) and 8 Jan. 1523 (see p. 144), without altering the year-date.
